First time posting up some in-progress hotshots! I shot this with a Didymium lens filter, on my 50mm macro lens. I really cant believe how well the filter was able to remove the sodium flare.
If you have ever tried to shoot the flame its typically very hard and heres why. When the super oxygen rich flame starts to heat up the glass molecules, sodium in the glass itself is heated or burned. This burn creates a bright yellow light that makes it difficult to see and photograph The solution is didymium, which is a mixture of the two elements praseodymium and neodymium. Together these two work together to block yellowish light around 589nm. It was discovered as eye protection by Sir William Crookes around 1913. 
This is my homie @daljar_glass killing it making a pocket mib he gifted me #daljarglass #glassscience #didymiumlens #headyart #degenerateart #bmr5003
